    <text>
        <body>            
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01023.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">

                <div2 type="document">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName>, Esq. Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>,</salute>
                        <salute>Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <p><persName>Daniel Fitzhugh</persName> of <placeName>Fairfax County, Va</placeName> having claim to service or labor of the undersigned, and having refused or failed to file in your office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the Act of Congress, entitled "An Act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>" approved <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>.</p>
                    <p>You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">12th July 1862</date>. The undersigned resided in <placeName>Washington</placeName> before and at the time of the passage of said act of <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date> with their late owners consent.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Description</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Sina Ellen Pearson</persName></cell>
                            <cell>female</cell>
                            <cell>26 years</cell>
                            <cell>Mulatto</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Martha Ann Hollis</persName></cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                            <cell>20 "</cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Lucretia Wilson</persName></cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                            <cell>51 "</cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Sina Ellen Hollis</persName> (child of <persName>Martha Ann</persName>)</cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                            <cell>6 months</cell>
                            <cell>"</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Sina Ellen Pearson</persName></signed>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Martha Ann Hollis</persName></signed>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Lucretia Wilson</persName></signed>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Sina Ellen Hollis</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness<lb/>
                        <signed><persName>J. Carter Marbury</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>                        
                                        
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01023.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>not paid</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>filed <date when="1862-07-29">29th July 1862</date>.</ab>
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No 2 folio <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#jc">64</unclear></ab>
                    </div3>
                                       
                    <div3 type="section">                        
                        <ab>Certificate refused, not coming under the law. the claimants admitted they ran away from a disloyal man who had hired her to <persName>Gen. Beauregard</persName></ab>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk of <choice><abbr>Com</abbr><expan>Commissioners</expan></choice></signed><lb/>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-08-05">Aug 5, 1862</date></dateline>
                            Witness<lb/>
                            <persName>Washington Wren</persName>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>                    
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01023.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                
                <dateline><date when="1862-08-05">Augt 5</date></dateline>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Sinah Ellen Pearson</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Martha Ann Hollis</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Lucretia Wilson</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Sina Ellen Hollis</persName></ab>
                    <ab>Servant of <persName>Daniel Fitzhugh</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Wash Wren</persName>. I do not know that I recognise servants. Yes I recognise <persName>Lucretia</persName> as belonging to my wifes sister <persName>Mrs Fitzhugh</persName>. If they are <persName>Mr Fitzhughs</persName> They are not here with his consent I do not believe he knows where they are</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Sinah Ellen</persName>. we came here without <persName>Mr Fitzhughs</persName> knowledge I was hired to <persName>Gen Beauregard</persName> &#38; came away last <date when="1862-03">March</date> when U.S. soldiers went up.</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>Certificate refused as not coming within law. Claimants admitting they had run away from a disloyal man</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01023.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Sinah E. Pearson</persName></ab>                        
                        <ab><persName>Martha A. Hollis</persName></ab>
                        <ab><persName>Lucretia Wilson</persName></ab>
                        <ab><persName>Sinah E. Hollis</persName></ab>
                        <ab><date when="1862-08-05">August 5</date>.</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                    <ab><date when="1862-08">Aug <gap reason="damage" extent="one number" unit="chars" quantity="1"/>th 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
